Narrative:
On January [XXX], 2025 at 10:31 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car in a parking garage at [XXX]. 
The Waymo AV was traveling in a parking garage off of [XXX] and approached a passenger car that was stopped, facing the wrong direction in the opposing lane of travel. The Waymo AV began to proceed straight, passing the passenger car, when the passenger car began to reverse, maneuvering into the Waymo AV's lane of travel, and the front passenger side of the passenger car made contact with the driver side of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The passenger car sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

Weather - Other Text: Collision was in an indoor, underground lot
Narrative:
On October [XXX], 2024 at 5:27 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (Waymo AV) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a van in an underground parking lot at [XXX].
Two Waymo AVs were stopped at neighboring junctures of a tight [XXX] of the lot. The first Waymo AV was preparing to make a right turn, while yielding to the other Waymo AV. While the Waymo AVs remained stopped, a van that had been traveling behind the first Waymo AV entered the oncoming lane to maneuver around the left side of the Waymo AV. The passenger side of the van then made contact with the rear driver side of the stopped Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AVs Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 1 of Standing General Order 2021-01 because a vehicle involved was towed away. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.
